Sentencas: Intermediate-temperature proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells often require impregnation techniques to improve the sluggish cathode reaction rate.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance enhancement of electrospun nanofiber cathode through impregnation method

Sentencas: Nevertheless, the limited impregnation efficiency poses a significant challenge.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance enhancement of electrospun nanofiber cathode through impregnation method

Sentencas: To tackle this issue, an innovative approach involving the synthesis of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3+d (LSCF) nanofibers (LSCF-NF) through electrospinning and their use as an impregnation substrate was employed.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance enhancement of electrospun nanofiber cathode through impregnation method

Sentencas: Through meticulous optimization of the skeleton microstructure, Bi0.75Ba0.25FeO3-d (BBF) was successfully impregnated in the LSCF substrate, leading to a remarkable enhancement of cell performance.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance enhancement of electrospun nanofiber cathode through impregnation method

Sentencas: Specifically, the cell performance improved from 680 mWcm-2 to an impressive 1350 mW cm-2 at 700 degrees C, underscoring the efficacy of this novel technique.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance enhancement of electrospun nanofiber cathode through impregnation method

Sentencas: The density functional theory (DFT) simulation confirms that BBF is beneficial for proton migration.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance enhancement of electrospun nanofiber cathode through impregnation method

Sentencas: The distribution of relaxation time method (DRT) analysis coupled with electrochemical impedance spectroscopy has revealed a noteworthy increase in oxygen adsorption and reduction rates following the implementation of impregnation combined with microstructure optimization.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance enhancement of electrospun nanofiber cathode through impregnation method

Sentencas: These results establish impregnation combined with microstructure optimization as a highly effective strategy for boosting the performance of fuel cells, paving the way for further advancements in this exciting field.
